     <div type="encomium">
   <head>Pray alwayes, <hi>Luke</hi> 18.</head>
   <l>DIstressed soul, if thou conceiv'st what 'tis</l>
   <l>To mount unto the tower of endlesse bliss<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>,</l>
   <l>Embrace this work: it reacheth to the skie,</l>
   <l>And higher, if beyond it ought do lie.</l>
   <l>Mans dull capacitie, weak humane sense,</l>
   <l>Wide worlds expansion, starres circumference,</l>
   <l>Cannot it comprehend: Prayer presseth even</l>
   <l>To Gods pavilion, to th' imperiall <gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
         <desc>•</desc>
      </gap>eaven.</l>
   <l>That is the golden chain fixt to Gods care:</l>
   <l>Knock, and hee'l open; call, and he will heare:</l>
   <l>This surely, this is blessed <hi>Jacobs ladder,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>On which our souls climbe by Christ to Christs Father:</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Faith</hi> is praiers chief attendant, <hi>Christ the way,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Gods Spirit both moves, &amp; helps how to pray:</l>
   <l>True love admittance gains, humble confession</l>
   <l>Both helps devotion, and procures remission.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Edmund Sheaf.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
